text: Pppffff. The rugby fans are currently in the stadium sorting domestic waste from recycling, singing the rocky road to Japan, at half time. There's a video.

@sdublincoco  the level of rubbish strewn about on lock view road, Clondalkin is an absolute disgrace. I counted eight different lots of refuse bins just dumped on the green. It’s disgusting - domestic waste, nappies, etc. Not sure if you’re aware but it needs to be cleaned

In the UK all recycling and domestic waste is free because are they paying property tax.  In Ireland the Irish are paying property tax We are still paying for our domestic waste and recycling charges . Thats a bit unfair.
DCC should definitely take back charge of domestic waste collection. It'd be better for the workers, the residents and the environment.

Went on the Ballycastle Loop walk today, one of Mayo’s network of promoted trails. Rubbish along entire route, including obviously tipped domestic waste. Even a microwave at one point! Tidy towns, filthy countryside
